+# raybrain eval harness
+
+Phase 1 plumbing for the Ragas-backed context-recall / context-precision
+gate. The golden set lives at `eval/golden/queries.yaml` (Ray-owned,
+hands-off).
+
+## `queries.yaml` format
+
+```yaml
+- query: "find every time I wrote about asymmetric objectives"
+  expected_sources:
+    - corpus_path: "plain-md/journal/2016-09.md"
+      lines: [45, 78]
+  notes: "the 2016 journal entry is the strongest match"
+```
+
+~10–20 queries, 1–5 expected sources each. The bot categorically cannot
+make this; Ray writes it once.
+
+## CLI
+
+```
+raybrain eval --gate context_recall=0.70 --golden eval/golden/queries.yaml
+```
+
+Phase 1 has no default retrieval engine — the subcommand exits non-zero
+after parsing until Ray wires one via `run_eval(retrieval_fn=...)`.
